President Trump held a roundtable discussion on the issue of MS-13, one of the most violent gangs in the world. The President emphasized the need for stronger border security and immigration reforms to combat the threat of MS-13. He called on Congress to close immigration loopholes that allow gang members to enter the country and to fund a border wall. The President also expressed his frustration with other countries that do not take back their citizens who are gang members and reiterated his commitment to cracking down on MS-13 and other violent gangs.